linguistic communities. Along with yielding rich qualitative data, the surveys generated revealing quantitative data that allows for comparisons based on gender, ethnicity, migration histories, region, age, income, and educational background. The book also brings Canada into international conversation with similar studies undertaken earlier in the United States, Australia, and Europe.Canadians and Their Pasts confirms that, for most Canadians, the past is not dead. Rather, it reveals that our histories continue to shape the present in many powerful ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aCollective memoryzCanada. 0aCollective memory--Canada. 0aHistoryxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aHistory--Social aspects--Canada. 0aInterviewszCanada. 0aInterviews--Canada. 0aMemoryxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aMemory--Social aspects--Canada. 0aPublic historyzCanada. 0aPublic history--Canada. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh1 aErcikan, Kadriye, eauthor.1 aFriesen, Gerald, eauthor.1 aMuise, D.A., eauthor.1 aNorthrup, David , eauthor.1 aSeixas, Peter, eauthor.40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442667648423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442667648.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG